  title = {Applying the {{Earth System Grid Security System}} in a {{Heterogeneous Environment}} of {{Data Access Services}}},
  volume = {12},
  abstract = {CEDA (Centre for Environmental Data Archival) based at STFC Rutherford Appleton Laboratory is host to
the BADC (British Atmospheric Data Centre) and NEODC (NERC Earth Observation Data Centre) with data
holdings of over half a Petabyte. In the coming months this figure is set to increase by over one Petabyte through
the BADC's role as one of three data centres to host the CMIP5 (Coupled Model Intercomparison Project Phase 5)
core archive of climate model data. Quite apart from the problem of managing the storage of such large volumes
